Merge pull request #81 from micbou/win-enter-nested

Enable nesting for the WinEnter autocommand

Enable nesting for the WinEnter autocommand

The WinEnter autocommand makes Vim automatically exit when NERDTree is
the last window. However, closing Vim this way will not trigger the
VimLeave event because autocommands do not nest by default. We need to
add the "nested" keyword for that.

Merge pull request #45 from techlivezheng/feature/source-cleaning

Docs fixes and cleanup

Make sure a NERDTree window gets opened in the new tab

Remove 's:MirrorIfGloballyActive()', use 's:NERDTreeMirrorOrCreate' instead.

Handle newly created tab separately in 'BufWinEnter' event

The 'TabEnter' event is triggered in the middle of establishing the new
buffer, it is not a good time to restore focus to NERDTree. At the time
when 'BufWinEnter' event gets triggered, the new buffer has been
successfully loaded, then we can restore the focus to NERDTree.
